eyebrow: FAQ
subtitle: "Common questions about the group, joining, and what happens next."
description: "FAQ for the I-PACE Owners' Advocacy Group — purpose, UK scope, legal status, privacy, and joining."
---

<div class="stack">

  <details>
    <summary>What is the group trying to achieve now?</summary>
    <div class="details-body">
      <p>Our preferred route is a constructive agreement. We are bringing owners together so
      JLR can understand the range of owner priorities and shape a fair offer that works for as
      many people as possible.</p>
      <p>We want to reach that outcome promptly, before Jaguar's next vehicle launch, so owners
      and JLR can be part of a positive way forward.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>What issues is the group focused on first?</summary>
    <div class="details-body">
      <p>The immediate focus is I-PACE traction battery faults, recall and customer notice work,
      warranty uncertainty, and inconsistent owner support. We are keeping the public launch
      simple, but those issues explain why owners need to organise now.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Is this another I-PACE forum?</summary>
    <div class="details-body">
      <p>No. Forums are useful places to exchange experiences. This group has a different job:
      to understand what owners need, represent those views clearly, and pursue a fair and
      consistent outcome.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Is this a legal action?</summary>
    <div class="details-body">
      <p>No. Joining this group does not make you a party to any legal claim. We are an informal
      owners' advocacy group. Our primary goal is to organise owners and engage constructively
      with JLR for fair outcomes.</p>
      <p>Other routes may be considered if constructive engagement fails. Any future legal
      proposal would be explained separately, and each owner would choose whether to take part.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Do you have legal counsel?</summary>
    <div class="details-body">
      <p>Yes. We have legal counsel within the group to help test the process and understand
      options. That expert input supports a credible constructive approach.</p>
      <p>It does not mean the group is currently running litigation or that joining creates legal
      representation. If any future legal route were proposed, it would be explained separately
      and would require each owner to choose deliberately.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Can members still pursue their own complaint or claim?</summary>
    <div class="details-body">
      <p>Yes. The group cannot stop individual owners from taking their own advice or pursuing
      their own consumer-rights routes. The purpose here is different: to keep the collective
      approach aligned, professional, and useful when speaking to JLR.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Is this anti-JLR?</summary>
    <div class="details-body">
      <p>No. We are advocates for I-PACE owners, not a campaign against JLR. We believe a
      constructive, evidence-led approach is more likely to produce results — and is better
      for the I-PACE community and for confidence in the car — than an adversarial stance.</p>
      <p>We want JLR to do the right thing. We organise to make it easier for them to do so, and
      harder for individual concerns to be ignored.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details data-site-mode-only="full">
    <summary>Will my VIN be made public?</summary>
    <div class="details-body">
      <p>No. Full VINs, email addresses, names, and registration numbers are never published.
      Our public evidence dashboard shows only anonymised, aggregate statistics.</p>
      <p>If you provide a VIN, it is processed server-side using an HMAC with a secret key.
      The full VIN is not stored; only the HMAC and final six characters are kept for
      deduplication and member-facing reference.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Will my personal data be shared?</summary>
    <div class="details-body">
      <p>For launch, we only ask for your name, email address, contact consent, and confirmation
      that joining is not a legal claim. We will not sell, rent, or share your personal data with
      third parties without your permission.</p>
      <p>If we later ask for vehicle details or structured evidence, we will explain what is
      needed, why it is useful, and how it may be used before you choose whether to provide it.</p>
      <p>See our <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a> for full details.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Can non-UK owners register interest?</summary>
    <div class="details-body">
      <p>Yes, but this is a UK-led initiative. Any approach to JLR, and any later legal
      representation if it were ever proposed, would be scoped around the relevant UK
      market and legal position.</p>
      <p>Owners elsewhere can register interest so we understand the wider picture. We may
      keep that information separate or share learning with another regional group if one
      forms.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details data-site-mode-only="full">
    <summary>What recalls are relevant?</summary>
    <div class="details-body">
      <p>The main recalls we are tracking are:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>H441</strong> — related battery campaign</li>
        <li><strong>H448</strong> — related battery campaign</li>
        <li><strong>H570</strong> — HV battery software and hardware recall</li>
        <li><strong>H571</strong> — related recall campaign</li>
        <li><strong>H572</strong> — related recall campaign</li>
      </ul>
      <p>If you have received recall correspondence or have had recall work carried out, we would
      like to know about it through the <a href="/member/submit-vehicle-data/">vehicle data form</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details data-site-mode-only="full">
    <summary>What is State of Health (SoH)?</summary>
    <div class="details-body">
      <p>State of Health (SoH) is a measure of a battery's capacity relative to its original
      design capacity. A new battery has 100% SoH. As batteries age and degrade, SoH falls.</p>
      <p>For the I-PACE's 90 kWh battery, a lower SoH means reduced real-world range. JLR has
      not publicly defined what level of degradation triggers warranty consideration, which is
      one reason we collect SoH data systematically.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Can I join without submitting vehicle data?</summary>
    <div class="details-body">
      <p>Yes. At launch we are only asking owners to register with their name and email address.
      If we later need vehicle details to support a specific report or proposal, we will explain
      what is needed and ask separately.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details data-site-mode-only="full">
    <summary>Why collect loan car, delay, payment and goodwill information?</summary>
    <div class="details-body">
      <p>Because inconsistency is itself a problem. If some owners receive suitable loan cars,
      prompt parts, and fair goodwill while others receive nothing — that is important to document.</p>
      <p>Structured data on loan car provision, delays, goodwill payments, and out-of-pocket costs
      helps us demonstrate the full impact of battery issues on owners' lives, and makes the
      case for consistent treatment across the fleet.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details data-site-mode-only="full">
    <summary>How will submitted data be verified?</summary>
    <div class="details-body">
      <p>Each submission is assigned a verification level:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Self-reported</strong> — owner's own statement, no documents supplied</li>
        <li><strong>Document supplied</strong> — owner has uploaded supporting paperwork</li>
        <li><strong>Reviewed</strong> — an organiser has reviewed the submission and documents</li>
        <li><strong>Duplicate-checked</strong> — confirmed not a duplicate entry</li>
        <li><strong>Excluded from public statistics</strong> — flagged as incomplete or inconsistent</li>
      </ul>
      <p>See our <a href="/methodology/">Methodology page</a> for full details.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details data-site-mode-only="full">
    <summary>Why do I need to sign in?</summary>
    <div class="details-body">
      <p>Sign-in (via Firebase Authentication) allows you to access a member dashboard, see your own
      submissions, and helps us prevent duplicate and fraudulent entries.</p>
      <p>You can browse public pages — the evidence dashboard, methodology, FAQ, updates —
      without signing in. Sign-in is only required to submit vehicle data or access member
      features.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

</div>
